\par In the Great Court, which stands as a patch of untouched peace among the fifty busy square miles devoted to the towering buildings that are the pulse }{\expnd-1\expndtw-7\cf1 beat of the United Worlds of the Galaxy, stands a statue.}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-6\cf1 It stands where it can look at the stars at night. There are other statues ringing the court, but this one stands in the center and alone.}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-7\cf1 It is not a very good statue. The face is too noble and lacks the lines of }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 living. The brow is a shade too high, the nose a shade too symmetrical, the }{\expnd-1\expndtw-5\cf1 
clothing a shade too carefully disposed. The whole bearing is by far too }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1 saintly to be true. One can suppose that the man in real life might have frowned at times, or hiccuped, but the statue seemed to insist that such }{
\expnd-2\expndtw-12\cf1 imperfections were impossible.}{
\par }{\expnd-2\expndtw-10\cf1 All this, of course, is understandable overcompensation. The man had no }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 statues raised to him while alive, and succeeding generations, with the ad\-vantage of hindsight, felt guilty.}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-6\cf1 The name on the pedestal reads "Richard Sayama Altmayer." Under\-}{\expnd-2\expndtw-10\cf1 neath it is a short phrase and, vertically arranged, three dates. The phrase is: }{\i\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 
"In a good cause, there are no failures."The }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 three dates are June 17, 2755; }{\expnd-1\expndtw-7\cf1 September 5, 2788; December 32, 2800;\emdash the years being counted in the }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 
usual manner of the period, that is, from the date of the first atomic explo\-}{\expnd-1\expndtw-7\cf1 sion in 1945 of the ancient era.}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1 None of those dates represents either his birth or death. They mark }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 neither a date of marriage or of the accomplishment of some great deed or, }{\expnd-1\expndtw-8\cf1 
indeed, of anything that the inhabitants of the United Worlds can remem}{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1 ber with pleasure and pride. Rather, they are the final expression of the }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 feeling of guilt.}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-6\cf1 Quite simply and plainly, they are the three dates upon which Richard }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 Sayama Altmayer was sent to prison for his opinions.}{
\par }{\expnd-2\expndtw-10\cf1 1\emdash }{\i\expnd-2\expndtw-10\cf1 lune 17, 2755}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-3\cf1\charscalex94 At the age of twenty-two, certainly, Dick Altmayer was fully capable of }{\cf1\charscalex94 feeling fury. His hair was as yet dark brown and he had not grown the }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 
mustache which, in later years, would be so characteristic of him. His nose }{\cf1\charscalex94 was, of course, thin and high-bridged, but the contours of his face were }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex94 
youthful. It would only be later that the growing gauntness of his cheeks would convert that nose into the prominent kndmark that it now is in the }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 minds of trillions of school children.}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex94 Geoffrey Stock was standing in the doorway, viewing the results of his }{\expnd-1\expndtw-5\cf1\charscalex94 friend's fury. His round face and cold, steady eyes were there, but he had yet }{
\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 to put on the first of the military uniforms in which he was to spend the rest }{\expnd-1\expndtw-5\cf1\charscalex94 of his life. }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 "'    He said, "Great Galaxy!"}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 Altmayer looked up. "Hello, Jeff."}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex94 "What's been happening, Dick? I thought your principles, pal, forbid destruction of any kind. Here's a book-viewer that looks somewhat de\-}{\expnd0\expndtw-3\cf1\charscalex94 stroyed." He picked up the pieces.}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-3\cf1\charscalex94 Altmayer said, "I was holding the viewer when my wave-receiver came }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 through with an official message. You know which one, too."}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex94 "I know. It happened to me, too. Where is it?"}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 "On the floor. I tore it off the spool as soon as it belched out at me. Wait, }{\cf1\charscalex94 let's dump it down the atom chute."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex94 "Hey, hold on. You can't\emdash "}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex94 "Why not?"}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 "Because you won't accomplish anything. You'll have to report."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 "And just why?"}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex94 "Don't be an ass, Dick."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex94 "This is a matter of principle, by Space."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex94 "Oh, nuts! You can't fight the whole planet."}{
\par }{\cf1\super\charscalex94 ;}{\cf1\charscalex94      "I don't intend to fight the whole planet; just the few who get us into }{\expnd-1\expndtw-8\cf1\charscalex94 wars."}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex94 Stock shrugged. "That means the whole planet. That guff of yours of }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex94 leaders tricking poor innocent people into fighting is just so much space-dust. Do you think that if a vot
e were taken the people wouldn't be over\-}{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 whelmingly in favor of fighting this fight?"}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex94 "That means nothing, Jeff. The government has control of\emdash "}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex94 "The organs of propaganda. Yes, I know. I've listened to you often }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex94 enough. But why not report, anyway?"}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-6\cf1\charscalex94 Altmayer turned away.}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex91 Stock said, "In the first place, you might not pass the physical examina\-}{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 tion."}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "I'd pass. I've been in Space."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex91 "That doesn't mean anything. If the doctors let you hop a liner, that only }{\cf1\charscalex91 means you don't have a heart murmur or an aneurysm. For military duty }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 
aboard ship in Space you need much more than just that. How do you know }{\expnd-1\expndtw-6\cf1\charscalex91 you qualify?"}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "That's a side issue, Jeff, and an insulting one. It's not that I'm afraid to }{\expnd0\expndtw-4\cf1\charscalex91 fight."}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "Do you think you can stop the war this way?"}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "I wish I could," Altrnayer's voice almost shook as he spoke. "It's this }{\expnd0\expndtw-3\cf1\charscalex91 idea I have that all mankind should be a single unit. There shouldn't be wars }{\cf1\charscalex91 
or space-fleets armed only for destruction. The Galaxy stands ready to be opened to the united efforts of the human race. Instead, we have been }{\expnd0\expndtw-3\cf1\charscalex91 
factioned for nearly two thousand years, and we throw away all the Galaxy."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex91 Stock laughed, "We're doing all right. There are more than eighty inde\-pendent planetary systems."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex91 "And are we the only intelligences in the Galaxy?"}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "Oh, the Diaboli, your particular devils," and Stock put his fists to his }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 temples and extended the two forefingers, waggling them.}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "And yours, too, and everybody's. They have a single government ex\-tending over more planets than all those occupied by our precious eighty }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 independents."}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "Sure, and their nearest planet is only fifteen hundred light years away }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex91 from Earth and they can't live on oxygen planets anyway."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex91 Stock got out of his friendly mood. He said, curtly, "Look, I dropped by }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 here to say that I was reporting for examination next week. Are you coming with me?"}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "No."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 "You're really determined."}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "I'm really determined."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 "You know you'll accomplish nothing. There'll be no great flame ignited on Earth. It will be no case of millions of young men being excited by your example into a no-war strike. You will simply be put in jail."}{

\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 "Well, then, jail it is."}{
\par }{\expnd0\expndtw-1\cf1\charscalex91 And jail it was. On June 17, 2755, of the atomic era, after a short trial in }{\cf1\charscalex91 which Richard Sayama Altmayer refused to present any defense, he was sentenced to jail fo
r the term of three years or for the duration of the war, whichever should be longer. He served a little over four years and two months, at which time the war ended in a definite though not shattering }{\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\charscalex91 
Santannian defeat. Earth gained complete control of certain disputed aster\-}{\cf1\charscalex91 oids, various commercial advantages, and a limitation of the Santannian }{\expnd-2\expndtw-12\cf1\charscalex91 navy.}{
\par }{\cf1\charscalex91 The combined human losses of the war were something over two thou-}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-5\cf1 sand ships with, of course, most of their crews, and in addition, several }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 millions of lives due to the bombardment of planetary surfaces from space. }{\expnd-1\expndtw-5\cf1 
The fleets of the two contending powers had been sufficiently strong to restrict this bombardment to the outposts of their respective systems, so }{\expnd-1\expndtw-7\cf1 that the planets of Earth and Santanni, themselves, were little affected.}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-6\cf1 The war conclusively established Earth as the strongest single human }{\expnd-2\expndtw-13\cf1 military power.}{
\par }{\expnd-1\expndtw-9\cf1 Geoffrey Stock fought throughout the war, seeing action more than once }{\expnd-1\expndtw-8\cf1 and remaining whole in life and limb despite that. At the end of the war he ha
d the rank of major. He took part in the first diplomatic mission sent out }{\expnd0\expndtw-3\cf1 by Earth to the worlds of the Diaboli, and that was the first step in his }{\expnd-1\expndtw-8\cf1 expanding role in Earth's military and political life.}{

